From 4029076622aa48e6c59114ebcc7e94ba15cca493 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Arun Vikas T <vikast@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 26 Sep 2025 16:07:50 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL:HOSTAPD: Add CLI support to dump SCS
 data

Add new CLI command `dump_scs` with subcommands:
  - `scs_list`: List all configured SCS sessions for a given STA
  - `scs_info <scs_id>`: Show detailed descriptor information for a
                         specific SCS ID

CLI and sample output:
1. hostapd_cli -i wlan0 dump_scs 00:4a:f5:42:32:61 scs_list

Configured SCS sessions for the client 00:4a:f5:42:32:61 are:
  Index: 0, SCS ID: 4

2. hostapd_cli -i wlan0 dump_scs 00:4a:f5:42:32:61 scs_info 4

SCS Info for STA: 00:4a:f5:42:32:61
Number of SCS Descriptors: 1

Descriptor type: QoS R3 Downlink
  SCS ID: 4
  Request Type: 0
  Intra Access Priority: 4
  TCLAS Processing: 0
  Number of TCLAS Elements: 1

  TCLAS Element 0:
    UP: 0
    Classifier Type: 4
    IP Version: 4
    Src IP: 0.0.0.0
    Dst IP: 0.0.0.0
    Protocol: 0
    Src Port: 0
    Dst Port: 5002
    DSCP: 0

  QoS Attributes:
    Direction: Downlink
    TID: 4
    UP: 4
    Bitmap: 0x0053
    Link ID: 0
    Min Service Interval: 20000 (us)
    Max Service Interval: 10000 (us)
    Min Data Rate: 96 (kbps)
    Delay Bound: 75000 (us)
    Max MSDU Size: 0
    Service Start Time: 0 (us)
    Service Start Time Link ID: 0
    Mean Data Rate: 0 (kbps)
    Burst Size: 50 (bytes)
    MSDU Lifetime: 0 (ms)
    MSDU Delivery Ratio: 10
    MSDU Count Exponent: 0
    Medium Time: 0 (256us/s)

